---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Anaesthetics — Program Requirements" description="ANZCA anaesthesia training program and assessment requirements.">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Program Requirements</h1>
    <p>Anaesthetics — ANZCA</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Introductory Training Assessments</h2>
    <p>New requirements as of <strong>1 January 2025</strong>. All must be completed during the 26-week IT phase.</p>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">MCQ Assessment</div>
      <p>60 questions · 60 minutes · 80% pass threshold · Unlimited attempts · Must complete by <strong>week 16</strong></p>
      <p style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Administered through Learn@ANZCA.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Specified Emergency Scenarios (SES)</div>
      <p>6 core topic areas · ~5–10 minutes each (~1 hour total) · Conducted by supervisors of training · No attempt limit · Assessed during final weeks</p>
    </div>

    <h3>Workplace-Based Assessments (WBAs)</h3>
    <div class="stat-grid">
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-number">3</div>
        <div class="stat-label">DOPs (Directly Observed Procedures)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-number">6</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Mini CEX (Clinical Evaluation Exercises)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-number">1</div>
        <div class="stat-label">MSF (Multisource Feedback)</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>Level 1 supervision is required until MCQ, SES, and all WBAs are completed.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Compulsory Course</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">EMAC — Effective Management of Anaesthetic Crises</div>
      <p>Simulation-based · 2.5 days · 5 modules covering human factors, airway management, cardiovascular emergencies, anaesthetic emergencies, and trauma.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Must complete before beginning Provisional Fellowship. Recommended after 12–18 months of experience. Not assessed — direct observational feedback only.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Progression Requirements</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">IT → Basic Training</div>
      <p>Complete all IT assessments (MCQ, SES, WBAs). Core unit review with supervisor.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Basic → Advanced Training</div>
      <p>Pass Primary Exam (PEx). Demonstrate competency in Clinical Fundamentals.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Advanced → Provisional Fellowship</div>
      <p>Complete all required Specialised Study Units (SSUs). Complete PCIA. Pass Final Exam (FEx). Secure approved PF position.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Provisional Fellowship → FANZCA</div>
      <p>Complete all PF requirements. DPA endorsement. Executive Committee approval. Register with AHPRA (AU) or MCNZ (NZ).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Leave & Interrupted Training</h2>
    <ul class="item-list">
      <li>Periods exceeding 12 continuous weeks require an interrupted training application</li>
      <li>Can sit Primary and Final exams within first 52 weeks of interrupted training if meeting eligibility</li>
      <li>Maximum 208 weeks at a single training site</li>
      <li>Public holidays count as clinical days regardless of whether worked</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</Layout>
